<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<ecore:EPackage xmi:version="2.0"
    xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
    xmlns:ecore="http://www.eclipse.org/emf/2002/Ecore" name="ows"
    nsURI="http://www.opengis.net/ows" nsPrefix="ows">
  <eAnnotations source="http://www.eclipse.org/emf/2002/GenModel">
    <details key="documentation" value="This XML Schema Document encodes the parts of ISO 19115 used by the common "ServiceIdentification" and "ServiceProvider" sections of the GetCapabilities operation response, known as the service metadata XML document. The parts encoded here are the MD_Keywords, CI_ResponsibleParty, and related classes. This XML Schema largely follows the current draft for ISO 19139, with the addition of documentation text extracted and edited from Annex B of ISO 19115. The UML package prefixes were omitted from XML names, and the XML element names were all capitalized, for consistency with other OWS Schemas. Also, the optional smXML:id attributes were omitted, as not being useful in a service metadata document.

		To obtain additional rights of use, visit http://www.opengeospatial.org/legal/ .
		

			GML 3.0 candidate xlinks schema. Copyright (c) 2001 OGC, All Rights Reserved.
		"/>
  </eAnnotations>
  <eAnnotations>
    <details key="appinfo" value="ows19115subset.xsd 2010-01-30"/>
  </eAnnotations>
  <eAnnotations source="urn:opengis:specification:gml:schema-xlinks:v3.0c2">
    <details key="appinfo" value="xlinks.xsd v3.0b2 2001-07"/>
  </eAnnotations>
  <eAnnotations source="http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace">
    <details key="lang" value="en"/>
  </eAnnotations>
  <eClassifiers xsi:type="ecore:EClass" name="AcceptFormatsType">
    <eAnnotations source="http://www.eclipse.org/emf/2002/GenModel">
      <details key="documentation" value="Prioritized sequence of zero or more GetCapabilities operation response formats desired by client, with preferred formats listed first. Each response format shall be identified by its MIME type. See AcceptFormats parameter use subclause for more information. "/>
    </eAnnotations>
    <eAnnotations source="http:///org/eclipse/emf/ecore/util/ExtendedMetaData">
      <details key="name" value="AcceptFormatsType"/>
      <details key="kind" value="elementOnly"/>
    </eAnnotations>
    <eStructuralFeatures xsi:type="ecore:EAttribute" name="outputFormat" unique="false"
        upperBound="-1" eType="#//MimeType">
      <eAnnotations source="http:///org/eclipse/emf/ecore/util/ExtendedMetaData">
        <details key="kind" value="element"/>
        <details key="name" value="OutputFormat"/>
        <details key="namespace" value="##targetNamespace"/>
      </eAnnotations>
    </eStructuralFeatures>
  </eClassifiers>
  <eClassifiers xsi:type="ecore:EClass" name="AcceptVersionsType">
    <eAnnotations source="http://www.eclipse.org/emf/2002/GenModel">
      <details key="documentation" value="Prioritized sequence of one or more specification versions accepted by client, with preferred versions listed first. See Version negotiation subclause for more information. "/>
    </eAnnotations>
    <eAnnotations source="http:///org/eclipse/emf/ecore/util/ExtendedMetaData">
      <details key="name" value="AcceptVersionsType"/>

    </eAnnotations>
    <eStructuralFeatures xsi:type="ecore:EAttribute" name="version" unique="false"
        lowerBound="1" upperBound="-1" eType="#//VersionType">
      <eAnnotations source="http:///org/eclipse/emf/ecore/util/ExtendedMetaData">
        <details key="kind" value="element"/>
        <details key="name" value="Version"/>
        <details key="namespace" value="##targetNamespace"/>
      </eAnnotations>
    </eStructuralFeatures>
  </eClassifiers>
  <eClassifiers xsi:type="ecore:EClass" name="AddressType">
    <eAnnotations source="http://www.eclipse.org/emf/2002/GenModel">
      <details key="documentation" value="Location of the responsible individual or organization. "/>
    </eAnnotations>
    <eAnnotations source="http:///org/eclipse/emf/ecore/util/ExtendedMetaData">
      <details key="name" value="AddressType"/>

    </eAnnotations>
    <eStructuralFeatures xsi:type="ecore:EAttribute" name="deliveryPoint" unique="false"

      <eAnnotations source="http:///org/eclipse/emf/ecore/util/ExtendedMetaData">

    <eStructuralFeatures xsi:type="ecore:EAttribute" name="city" eType="ecore:EDataType http://www.eclipse.org/emf/2003/XMLType#//String">
      <eAnnotations source="http://www.eclipse.org/emf/2002/GenModel">
        <details key="documentation" value="City of the location. "/>
      </eAnnotations>
      <eAnnotations source="http:///org/eclipse/emf/ecore/util/ExtendedMetaData">
        <details key="kind" value="element"/>
        <details key="name" value="City"/>
        <details key="namespace" value="##targetNamespace"/>
      </eAnnotations>
    </eStructuralFeatures>
    <eStructuralFeatures xsi:type="ecore:EAttribute" name="administrativeArea" eType="ecore:EDataType http://www.eclipse.org/emf/2003/XMLType#//String">
      <eAnnotations source="http://www.eclipse.org/emf/2002/GenModel">
        <details key="documentation" value="State or province of the location. "/>
      </eAnnotations>
      <eAnnotations source="http:///org/eclipse/emf/ecore/util/ExtendedMetaData">
        <details key="kind" value="element"/>
        <details key="name" value="AdministrativeArea"/>

      </eAnnotations>

      <eAnnotations source="http://www.eclipse.org/emf/2002/GenModel">
        <details key="documentation" value="ZIP or other postal code. "/>
      </eAnnotations>
      <eAnnotations source="http:///org/eclipse/emf/ecore/util/ExtendedMetaData">
        <details key="kind" value="element"/>
        <details key="name" value="PostalCode"/>

      </eAnnotations>

      <eAnnotations source="http://www.eclipse.org/emf/2002/GenModel">
        <details key="documentation" value="Country of the physical address. "/>
      </eAnnotations>

        <details key="name" value="Country"/>

      </eAnnotations>

    <eStructuralFeatures xsi:type="ecore:EAttribute" name="electronicMailAddress"
        unique="false" upperBound="-1" eType="ecore:EDataType http://www.eclipse.org/emf/2003/XMLType#//String">
      <eAnnotations source="http://www.eclipse.org/emf/2002/GenModel">
        <details key="documentation" value="Address of the electronic mailbox of the responsible organization or individual. "/>
      </eAnnotations>
      <eAnnotations source="http:///org/eclipse/emf/ecore/util/ExtendedMetaData">
        <details key="kind" value="element"/>
        <details key="name" value="ElectronicMailAddress"/>
        <details key="namespace" value="##targetNamespace"/>
      </eAnnotations>
    </eStructuralFeatures>
  </eClassifiers>
  <eClassifiers xsi:type="ecore:EClass" name="BoundingBoxType">
    <eAnnotations source="http://www.eclipse.org/emf/2002/GenModel">
      <details key="documentation" value="XML encoded minimum rectangular bounding box (or region) parameter, surrounding all the associated data. 
This type is adapted from the EnvelopeType of GML 3.1, with modified contents and documentation for encoding a MINIMUM size box SURROUNDING all associated data. "/>
    </eAnnotations>
    <eAnnotations source="http:///org/eclipse/emf/ecore/util/ExtendedMetaData">
      <details key="name" value="BoundingBoxType"/>
      <details key="kind" value="elementOnly"/>
    </eAnnotations>
    <eStructuralFeatures xsi:type="ecore:EAttribute" name="lowerCorner" lowerBound="1"
        eType="#//PositionType">
      <eAnnotations source="http://www.eclipse.org/emf/2002/GenModel">
        <details key="documentation" value="Position of the bounding box corner at which the value of each coordinate normally is the algebraic minimum within this bounding box. In some cases, this position is normally displayed at the top, such as the top left for some image coordinates. For more information, see Subclauses 10.2.5 and C.13. "/>
      </eAnnotations>
      <eAnnotations source="http:///org/eclipse/emf/ecore/util/ExtendedMetaData">
        <details key="kind" value="element"/>
        <details key="name" value="LowerCorner"/>
        <details key="namespace" value="##targetNamespace"/>
      </eAnnotations>
    </eStructuralFeatures>
    <eStructuralFeatures xsi:type="ecore:EAttribute" name="upperCorner" lowerBound="1"
        eType="#//PositionType">
      <eAnnotations source="http://www.eclipse.org/emf/2002/GenModel">
        <details key="documentation" value="Position of the bounding box corner at which the value of each coordinate normally is the algebraic maximum within this bounding box. In some cases, this position is normally displayed at the bottom, such as the bottom right for some image coordinates. For more information, see Subclauses 10.2.5 and C.13. "/>
      </eAnnotations>
      <eAnnotations source="http:///org/eclipse/emf/ecore/util/ExtendedMetaData">
        <details key="kind" value="element"/>
        <details key="name" value="UpperCorner"/>
        <details key="namespace" value="##targetNamespace"/>
      </eAnnotations>
    </eStructuralFeatures>
    <eStructuralFeatures xsi:type="ecore:EAttribute" name="crs" eType="ecore:EDataType http://www.eclipse.org/emf/2003/XMLType#//AnyURI">
      <eAnnotations source="http://www.eclipse.org/emf/2002/GenModel">
        <details key="documentation" value="Usually references the definition of a CRS, as specified in [OGC Topic 2]. Such a CRS definition can be XML encoded using the gml:CoordinateReferenceSystemType in [GML 3.1]. For well known references, it is not required that a CRS definition exist at the location the URI points to. If no anyURI value is included, the applicable CRS must be either:
a)	Specified outside the bounding box, but inside a data structure that includes this bounding box, as specified for a specific OWS use of this bounding box type.
b)	Fixed and specified in the Implementation Specification for a specific OWS use of the bounding box type. "/>
      </eAnnotations>
      <eAnnotations source="http:///org/eclipse/emf/ecore/util/ExtendedMetaData">
        <details key="kind" value="attribute"/>
        <details key="name" value="crs"/>
      </eAnnotations>
    </eStructuralFeatures>
    <eStructuralFeatures xsi:type="ecore:EAttribute" name="dimensions" eType="ecore:EDataType http://www.eclipse.org/emf/2003/XMLType#//PositiveInteger">
      <eAnnotations source="http://www.eclipse.org/emf/2002/GenModel">
        <details key="documentation" value="The number of dimensions in this CRS (the length of a coordinate sequence in this use of the PositionType). This number is specified by the CRS definition, but can also be specified here. "/>
      </eAnnotations>
      <eAnnotations source="http:///org/eclipse/emf/ecore/util/ExtendedMetaData">
        <details key="kind" value="attribute"/>
        <details key="name" value="dimensions"/>
      </eAnnotations>
    </eStructuralFeatures>
  </eClassifiers>
  <eClassifiers xsi:type="ecore:EClass" name="CapabilitiesBaseType">
    <eAnnotations source="http://www.eclipse.org/emf/2002/GenModel">
      <details key="documentation" value="XML encoded GetCapabilities operation response. This document provides clients with service metadata about a specific service instance, usually including metadata about the tightly-coupled data served. If the server does not implement the updateSequence parameter, the server shall always return the complete Capabilities document, without the updateSequence parameter. When the server implements the updateSequence parameter and the GetCapabilities operation request included the updateSequence parameter with the current value, the server shall return this element with only the "version" and "updateSequence" attributes. Otherwise, all optional elements shall be included or not depending on the actual value of the Contents parameter in the GetCapabilities operation request. This base type shall be extended by each specific OWS to include the additional contents needed. "/>
    </eAnnotations>
    <eAnnotations source="http:///org/eclipse/emf/ecore/util/ExtendedMetaData">
      <details key="name" value="CapabilitiesBaseType"/>
      <details key="kind" value="elementOnly"/>
    </eAnnotations>
    <eStructuralFeatures xsi:type="ecore:EReference" name="serviceIdentification"
        eType="#//ServiceIdentificationType" containment="true" resolveProxies="false">
      <eAnnotations source="http://www.eclipse.org/emf/2002/GenModel">
        <details key="documentation" value="General metadata for this specific server. This XML Schema of this section shall be the same for all OWS. "/>
      </eAnnotations>
      <eAnnotations source="http:///org/eclipse/emf/ecore/util/ExtendedMetaData">
        <details key="kind" value="element"/>
        <details key="name" value="ServiceIdentification"/>
        <details key="namespace" value="##targetNamespace"/>
      </eAnnotations>
    </eStructuralFeatures>
    <eStructuralFeatures xsi:type="ecore:EReference" name="serviceProvider" eType="#//ServiceProviderType"
        containment="true" resolveProxies="false">
      <eAnnotations source="http://www.eclipse.org/emf/2002/GenModel">
        <details key="documentation" value="Metadata about the organization that provides this specific service instance or server. "/>
      </eAnnotations>
      <eAnnotations source="http:///org/eclipse/emf/ecore/util/ExtendedMetaData">
        <details key="kind" value="element"/>
        <details key="name" value="ServiceProvider"/>
        <details key="namespace" value="##targetNamespace"/>
      </eAnnotations>
    </eStructuralFeatures>
    <eStructuralFeatures xsi:type="ecore:EReference" name="operationsMetadata" eType="#//OperationsMetadataType"
        containment="true" resolveProxies="false">
      <eAnnotations source="http://www.eclipse.org/emf/2002/GenModel">
        <details key="documentation" value="Metadata about the operations and related abilities specified by this service and implemented by this server, including the URLs for operation requests. The basic contents of this section shall be the same for all OWS types, but individual services can add elements and/or change the optionality of optional elements. "/>
      </eAnnotations>
      <eAnnotations source="http:///org/eclipse/emf/ecore/util/ExtendedMetaData">
        <details key="kind" value="element"/>
        <details key="name" value="OperationsMetadata"/>
        <details key="namespace" value="##targetNamespace"/>
      </eAnnotations>
    </eStructuralFeatures>
    <eStructuralFeatures xsi:type="ecore:EAttribute" name="updateSequence" eType="#//UpdateSequenceType">
      <eAnnotations source="http:///org/eclipse/emf/ecore/util/ExtendedMetaData">
        <details key="kind" value="attribute"/>
        <details key="name" value="updateSequence"/>
      </eAnnotations>
    </eStructuralFeatures>
    <eStructuralFeatures xsi:type="ecore:EAttribute" name="version" lowerBound="1"
        eType="#//VersionType">
      <eAnnotations source="http:///org/eclipse/emf/ecore/util/ExtendedMetaData">
        <details key="kind" value="attribute"/>
        <details key="name" value="version"/>
      </eAnnotations>
    </eStructuralFeatures>
  </eClassifiers>
  <eClassifiers xsi:type="ecore:EClass" name="CodeType">
    <eAnnotations source="http://www.eclipse.org/emf/2002/GenModel">
      <details key="documentation" value="Name or code with an (optional) authority. If the codeSpace attribute is present, its value should reference a dictionary, thesaurus, or authority for the name or code, such as the organisation who assigned the value, or the dictionary from which it is taken. 
Type copied from basicTypes.xsd of GML 3 with documentation edited, for possible use outside the ServiceIdentification section of a service metadata document. "/>
    </eAnnotations>
    <eAnnotations source="http:///org/eclipse/emf/ecore/util/ExtendedMetaData">
      <details key="name" value="CodeType"/>
      <details key="kind" value="simple"/>
    </eAnnotations>
    <eStructuralFeatures xsi:type="ecore:EAttribute" name="value" eType="ecore:EDataType http://www.eclipse.org/emf/2003/XMLType#//String">
      <eAnnotations source="http:///org/eclipse/emf/ecore/util/ExtendedMetaData">
        <details key="name" value=":0"/>
        <details key="kind" value="simple"/>
      </eAnnotations>
    </eStructuralFeatures>
    <eStructuralFeatures xsi:type="ecore:EAttribute" name="codeSpace" eType="ecore:EDataType http://www.eclipse.org/emf/2003/XMLType#//AnyURI">
      <eAnnotations source="http:///org/eclipse/emf/ecore/util/ExtendedMetaData">
        <details key="kind" value="attribute"/>
        <details key="name" value="codeSpace"/>
      </eAnnotations>
    </eStructuralFeatures>
  </eClassifiers>
  <eClassifiers xsi:type="ecore:EClass" name="ContactType">
    <eAnnotations source="http://www.eclipse.org/emf/2002/GenModel">
      <details key="documentation" value="Information required to enable contact with the responsible person and/or organization. 
For OWS use in the service metadata document, the optional hoursOfService and contactInstructions elements were retained, as possibly being useful in the ServiceProvider section. "/>
    </eAnnotations>
    <eAnnotations source="http:///org/eclipse/emf/ecore/util/ExtendedMetaData">
      <details key="name" value="ContactType"/>
      <details key="kind" value="elementOnly"/>
    </eAnnotations>
    <eStructuralFeatures xsi:type="ecore:EReference" name="phone" eType="#//TelephoneType"
        containment="true" resolveProxies="false">
      <eAnnotations source="http://www.eclipse.org/emf/2002/GenModel">
        <details key="documentation" value="Telephone numbers at which the organization or individual may be contacted. "/>
      </eAnnotations>
      <eAnnotations source="http:///org/eclipse/emf/ecore/util/ExtendedMetaData">
        <details key="kind" value="element"/>
        <details key="name" value="Phone"/>
        <details key="namespace" value="##targetNamespace"/>
      </eAnnotations>
    </eStructuralFeatures>
    <eStructuralFeatures xsi:type="ecore:EReference" name="address" eType="#//AddressType"
        containment="true" resolveProxies="false">
      <eAnnotations source="http://www.eclipse.org/emf/2002/GenModel">
        <details key="documentation" value="Physical and email address at which the organization or individual may be contacted. "/>
      </eAnnotations>
      <eAnnotations source="http:///org/eclipse/emf/ecore/util/ExtendedMetaData">
        <details key="kind" value="element"/>
        <details key="name" value="Address"/>
        <details key="namespace" value="##targetNamespace"/>
      </eAnnotations>
    </eStructuralFeatures>
    <eStructuralFeatures xsi:type="ecore:EReference" name="onlineResource" eType="#//OnlineResourceType"
        containment="true" resolveProxies="false">
      <eAnnotations source="http://www.eclipse.org/emf/2002/GenModel">
        <details key="documentation" value="On-line information that can be used to contact the individual or organization. OWS specifics: The xlink:href attribute in the xlink:simpleLink attribute group shall be used to reference this resource. Whenever practical, the xlink:href attribute with type anyURI should be a URL from which more contact information can be electronically retrieved. The xlink:title attribute with type "string" can be used to name this set of information. The other attributes in the xlink:simpleLink attribute group should not be used. "/>
      </eAnnotations>
      <eAnnotations source="http:///org/eclipse/emf/ecore/util/ExtendedMetaData">
        <details key="kind" value="element"/>
        <details key="name" value="OnlineResource"/>
        <details key="namespace" value="##targetNamespace"/>
      </eAnnotations>
    </eStructuralFeatures>
    <eStructuralFeatures xsi:type="ecore:EAttribute" name="hoursOfService" eType="ecore:EDataType http://www.eclipse.org/emf/2003/XMLType#//String">
      <eAnnotations source="http://www.eclipse.org/emf/2002/GenModel">
        <details key="documentation" value="Time period (including time zone) when individuals can contact the organization or individual. "/>
      </eAnnotations>
      <eAnnotations source="http:///org/eclipse/emf/ecore/util/ExtendedMetaData">
        <details key="kind" value="element"/>
        <details key="name" value="HoursOfService"/>
        <details key="namespace" value="##targetNamespace"/>
      </eAnnotations>
    </eStructuralFeatures>
    <eStructuralFeatures xsi:type="ecore:EAttribute" name="contactInstructions" eType="ecore:EDataType http://www.eclipse.org/emf/2003/XMLType#//String">
      <eAnnotations source="http://www.eclipse.org/emf/2002/GenModel">
        <details key="documentation" value="Supplemental instructions on how or when to contact the individual or organization. "/>
      </eAnnotations>
      <eAnnotations source="http:///org/eclipse/emf/ecore/util/ExtendedMetaData">
        <details key="kind" value="element"/>
        <details key="name" value="ContactInstructions"/>
        <details key="namespace" value="##targetNamespace"/>
      </eAnnotations>
    </eStructuralFeatures>
  </eClassifiers>
  <eClassifiers xsi:type="ecore:EClass" name="DCPType">
    <eAnnotations source="http:///org/eclipse/emf/ecore/util/ExtendedMetaData">
      <details key="name" value="DCP_._type"/>
      <details key="kind" value="elementOnly"/>
    </eAnnotations>
    <eStructuralFeatures xsi:type="ecore:EReference" name="hTTP" eType="#//HTTPType"
        containment="true" resolveProxies="false">
      <eAnnotations source="http://www.eclipse.org/emf/2002/GenModel">
        <details key="documentation" value="Connect point URLs for the HTTP Distributed Computing Platform (DCP). Normally, only one Get and/or one Post is included in this element. More than one Get and/or Post is allowed to support including alternative URLs for uses such as load balancing or backup. "/>
      </eAnnotations>
      <eAnnotations source="http:///org/eclipse/emf/ecore/util/ExtendedMetaData">
        <details key="kind" value="element"/>
        <details key="name" value="HTTP"/>
        <details key="namespace" value="##targetNamespace"/>
      </eAnnotations>
    </eStructuralFeatures>

    </eAnnotations>
    <eAnnotations source="http:///org/eclipse/emf/ecore/util/ExtendedMetaData">
      <details key="name" value="DescriptionType"/>

        <details key="kind" value="element"/>

      <eAnnotations source="http://www.eclipse.org/emf/2002/GenModel">
        <details key="documentation" value="Brief narrative description of this resource, normally used for display to a human. "/>
      </eAnnotations>
      <eAnnotations source="http:///org/eclipse/emf/ecore/util/ExtendedMetaData">
        <details key="kind" value="element"/>
        <details key="name" value="Abstract"/>
        <details key="namespace" value="##targetNamespace"/>
      </eAnnotations>

        <details key="name" value="Keywords"/>
